Comment (src/views/admin/NotificationsView.vue:589):
**🟡 BUG-UI-2: `healthWarnings` produces duplicate warnings.**

This computed currently aggregates three sources:
1. `health.value?.warnings` — the top-level warnings array returned by the API (line 565)
2. UI-generated `missing_destination_*` warnings for any notification with an empty `configuredDestinations` (lines 580–588)
3. `notification.warnings` from each notification item (line 589)

The problem: the API already aggregates per-notification warnings into the top-level `health.warnings` array (see `healthWarnings()` in `internal/service/notificationtroubleshooting/service.go`, which appends `item.Warnings...` to the top-level slice). So sources 2 and 3 here are duplicates of source 1 — every per-notification warning appears twice.

During e2e testing this produced a wall of repeated warnings in the Health tab (e.g. `missing_destination` for TASK_AVAILABLE shown twice, `missing_destination` for EVIDENCE_DIGEST shown twice).

**Fix:** remove sources 2 and 3 entirely. Rely solely on `health.value?.warnings` for all warning content:

```ts
const healthWarnings = computed(() => {
  const warnings: NotificationHealthWarning[] = [
    ...(health.value?.warnings ?? []),
  ];
  // stale / discarded / schedule checks remain here (they are UI-side enrichments)
  ...
  return warnings;
});
```
